name: Harrison Square Presbyterian Church
vaccines: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine, Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine
info:
****This is a JOHNSON & JOHNSON single dose vaccine clinic. **** and is by appointment or walk in. ++Pfizer vaccine will also be available. ++ 
Please note: Johnson & Johnson vaccine can only be administered to individuals 18 years of age or older according CDC requirements. Pfizer can be administered to youth ages 16 to 17 if accompanied by an adult who can sign a parental consent form.

This clinic is located at and hosted by Harrison Square Presbyterian Church in partnership with Lewis County DPHSS, WA DOH and WA National Guard. This is a walk in location. Please let us know if you or someone you are accompanying needs assistance of any kind.  **You should also plan your visit around waiting for 15 minutes in the observation area so we can monitor for any unlikely adverse reactions to the vaccine.** Certain people with pre-identified conditions or past anaphylaxis events may be asked to wait for 30 minutes of observation.

Free language translation services are provided. Video ASL translation is also provided.

If this is your 2nd dose Pfizer vaccination please bring your vaccination card from your 1st dose. If you do not have your card you may register with and confirm proof of vaccination at https://wa.myir.net/                      
 Please do not come if you are feeling ill. Please arrive as close as possible to your scheduled time to prevent crowding that will impede appropriate social distancing. - It is best to wear clothes that will allow for access to your upper arm, just below the shoulder. Given Washington's commitment to equitable and fair access, those seeking COVID-19 vaccines at this clinic location must either live or work in Washington state. If you do not live or work in Washington, please do not make an appointment or travel to this site.  **Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Hawker Center for Integrative Medicine - COVID Vaccine Clinic
address: 1750 112th Avenue Northeast, STE C-102, Bellevue WA, 98004
info:
Please read the following important information below:
***We currently have the ability to provide the 1st and 2nd doses of Moderna.***
Please sign up for an appointment time.  

When you arrive to the clinic, please continue to wear your face covering, practice physical distancing and wash your hands frequently to help reduce transmission.

Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. 
Expect to stay for 15 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. 

Due to the limited supplies of vaccines provided to us each week, we are unable to take walk-ins, so please make an appointment. 

***Directions to the Hawker Center for Integrative Medicine:***
Our clinic is located in the Hidden Valley Office Complex.
1) When you arrive at the complex, take either driveway all the way to the back of the building.
2) We are located on the prominent corner at the very back of the building and we have our own private entrance.  Look for the parking lot with the number "2" in a big steel frame.  Do NOT go into the main building for we have a private entrance accessible directly from the parking lot. 
Look for our sign with our logo in the window and a door with the number "C-102" on it, visible from the parking lot.

*If you would like to find out more information about our clinic, please visit our website at www.hawkerhealth.com

info:
This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 16 and older. 

• This is a drive-thru clinic at Thurston County Fairgrounds, 2705 Carpenter Rd SE, Olympia 98503  . • All minors 16 and 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with warm layers. • Please arrive at your scheduled appointment time. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
